testDataType

public void testDataType(XSDatatypeImpl baseType,
                         String[] values,
                         String[] wrongs,
                         String baseAnswer,
                         TestPattern pattern,
                         boolean completenessOnly)
                  throws Exception
tests one datatype

Parameters:
typeObj - DataType object to be tested
answer - default answer sheet for values parameter. each "o" indicates valid, whereas "." indicates invalid. answer.charAt(i) indicates validity of values[i],
values - possibly valid values. These values are tested against DataType object.
wrongs - values which are always wrong. But they are tested anyway.
pattern - test pattern generator that iterates a combination of facets and its predicted result.
completenessOnly - true indicates test is only performed for completeness; that is, make sure that answer is 'o' for those which is marked as 'o'. this flag is used to test union types.
Throws:
Exception
